action.content:
Based on the room description and the available direction, the next action would be to move east. The graph will be updated to reflect this new room's connection possibilities. The node names are based on the common nomenclature of the types of rooms described.

```
{
"action": "GO: east",
"description": "We are in a living room with two sofas, a coffee table, a fireplace, and a TV.",
"graph": {
"nodes": ["Living Room"],
"edges": {
"north": [],
"south": [],
"east": [],
"west": []
}
}
}
```
If the next instruction results in a room with northward options, the graph will be updated to include that connection accordingly. If there are no new rooms to visit, the action would be "DONE."
